<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A 14-month old toddler has died after being run over by a car in rural Victoria.</p>

<p>A car was turning toward a slip lane on High Street in Kangaroo Flat, a south-western suburb of Bendigo, when it collided with the child about 7.20pm on Wednesday.</p>

<p>The 14-month-old child suffered critical injuries and was rushed to hospital and later died. </p>

<p>A car was turning toward a slip lane on High Street in Kangaroo Flats, 5km south-west of Bendigo's CBD when it collided with the child about 7.20pm on Wednesday </p>

<p>The 56-year-old driver of the car stopped at the scene to help and was helping police with their investigations. </p>

<p>A total of 152 people have died on Victoria's roads compared to 188 this time last year. </p>

<p>Anyone who may have witnessed the tragedy or have dash cam footage is urged to come forward or contact Crime Stoppers on 1800 333 000.  </p>

